INSERT INTO `music_sargams` (`id`,`song_names`,`sargam`,`url`) VALUES (393,'Ye Awara Raatein - Notes & Sargam','Sargam for ghazal Ye Awara Raatein (1959)\n Singer : Manna De\n Lyrics : Madhukar Rajasthani\n Music : V Balsara\nye | aawaara | raatein\n (N)~R |┬á R RG G | G R .N\nye | khoyi | si | baatein\n (N)~R |┬á R RG | G | G R .N\nye | uljhaa | sa | mausam\n .D.N | .P.P | .D | .N S\nye | nazron | ki | ghaaten\n SG | R R | S | .D.N\nkahaan | aa | gaye | ham\n PD | DN | P M | M~G\nkahaan | jaa | rahe | the\n PM | G | R S | R\nkahaan | aa | gaye | ham\n PD | DN | P M | M~GPMG\nkahaan | jaa | rahe | the\n PM | G | R S | R ~ .N\nYe Awara RaateinÔÇª\nye | naagan | se | bal kaaye\n P | P P | PM | G R G~R G~R\nye | khwaabon | ke | saaye\n RP | P P | PM | G R G~R\nye | chhitke | se | taare\n R | G P D | NSÔÇÖ | SÔÇÖRÔÇÖ~SÔÇÖ\njo | palkon | pe | chhaaye\n SÔÇÖ | S N D | P | D N\nkahaan | aa | gaye | ham\n PD | DN | P M | M~G\nkahaan | jaa | rahe | the\n PM | G | R S | R\nkahaan | aa | gaye | ham\n PD | DN | P M | M~GPMG\nkahaan | jaa | rahe | the\n PM | G | R S | R ~ .N\nYe Awara RaateinÔÇª\nye soyi si galiyaan\n ye kumbhlaayee kaliyaan\n ye aankhon ke bhanwre\n kare rangraliyaan\n kahaan aa gaye ham\n kahaan jaa rahe thhe\n ye aawaara raatein\n ye khoyi si baatein\n ye uljhaa sa mausam\n ye nazron ke ghaaten\nye bikhri hawaayen\n jo tooti si aahen\n bulaaye sabhi ko\n nazaaron ki baahen\n kahaan aa gaye ham\n kahaan jaa rahe thhe\n kahaan aa gaye ham\n kahaan jaa rahe thhe\n hmmn hmmn\n','Notes---Sargam-Ye-Awara-Raatein');
INSERT INTO `music_sargams` (`id`,`song_names`,`sargam`,`url`) VALUES (394,'Yamma Yamma - Notes & Sargam','Yamma Yamma Sargam notations\n Singer : R D Burman, Mohd Rafi\n lyrics : Anand Bakshi\n Music : R D Burman\n Movie : Shaan (1980)\nIf you wish to know what is ÔÇÿmusic arrangementÔÇÖ in a song, then take this song as a reference.┬á Brilliant composition by RD, as usual!┬á I wrote down the Sargam notations for this song in just 15 minutes flat! But that was only the vocal part.┬á When next day, I sat down to write the prelude and interlude parts of this song, believe me it took me 6 hours to do so.┬á The prelude part is over a minute long.┬á Although I have tried my best to include all parts of this song, but if you find a note or two missing, please pardon me.\nI produced the notes by playing this song on my F# flute.┬á Re, Ga and Da swars for this song on this scale are all Komal (Flat notes).┬á So, here it is.┬á Just first listen to this song for a couple of times and then try out the following sargam notations.┬á Hope youÔÇÖll enjoy!┬á Good luck.\n','Notes---Sargam-Yamma-Yamma');
