INSERT INTO `music_sargams` (`id`,`song_names`,`sargam`,`url`) VALUES (452,'Puchho na kaise maine rain bitai - Notes & Sargam','Sargam (Notation) for song: Puchho na kaise maine rain bitai\n Singer : Manna De\n Music : S D Burman\n Lyrics : Shailendra\n Film : Meri Surat Teri Ankhen (1963)\nPuchho | na | kaise | maine | rain | bitai\n SSÔÇÖD | D | D(N)D | PM | M~G | Mr~S\nIk | pal | jaise, | ik | jug | beeta\n rS | .D.n | rS | Sr | MM | M~M(PMGr)\nIk pal jaise, ik jug beeta\n rS | .D.n | rS | Sr | MM | M~M\nJug | beete | mohe | neend | na | aayi\n MD | DDNSÔÇÖ | nD | MG | M | rS\nPuchho | na | kaise | maine | rain | bitai\n SSÔÇÖD | D | D(N)D | PM | M~G | Mr~S\nUt | jale | deepak | it | man | mera\n MM | MM | DÔÇöPM | PD | nÔÇÖSÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖSÔÇÖ\nPhir | bhi | na | jaye | mere | ghar | ka | andhera\n rÔÇÖrÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖ rÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖrÔÇÖ | SÔÇÖrÔÇÖ | M | GrS\nUt | jale | deepak | it | man | mera\n MM | MM | DÔÇöPM | PD | nÔÇÖSÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖSÔÇÖ\nmanÔÇª.. meraÔÇª.. mera ÔÇª..\n MMÔÇö (to improvise)\nUt | jale | deepak | it | man | mera\n MM | MM | DÔÇöPM | PD | nÔÇÖSÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖSÔÇÖ\nPhir | bhi | na | jaye | mere | ghar | ka | andhera\n rÔÇÖrÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖ rÔÇÖ | rÔÇÖrÔÇÖ | SÔÇÖrÔÇÖ | M | GrS\nTadpat tarsat umar gawayi\n Srnn | nSn(P)n | PMG | MrS\nPuchho na kaise maine rain bitai\n https://youtu.be/TUuxvHDD9as\n','Notes---Sargam-Puchho-na-kaise-maine-rain-bitai');
INSERT INTO `music_sargams` (`id`,`song_names`,`sargam`,`url`) VALUES (453,'Piya to se naina lage re - Notes & Sargam','Sargam notations for the song Piya To se Nainaa Laage Re\n Singer: Lata\n Music : SD Burman\n Movie: Guide (1965)\nPiyaa | Tose| Nainaa| Laage| Re, \n MM | P N | PM | G~R R | GM\nNainaa | Laage | Re\n MM | P D(N)D | P~M~G\nJaane | Kyaa | Ho | Ab | Aage | Re\n MM | P | D(N)D | PM | G~R R | GM\nNainaa | Laage | Re\n MM | P D P | P~SNDP\nPiyaa | Tose| Nainaa| Laage| Re, \n MM | P N | PM | G~R R | GM\nBhor | ki | bela | suhani \n R G | R | G~R R | GR G~R\nnadiya | ke | teerey.\n DD~P~M | G~R | GM\nbhar | ke | ghagar | jis | ghadi | main \n D | N | D N~D | D | ND | N~D\nchalun | dheere | dheere.\n (S)R\' R\'~S\' | N D P M | PP MD\na, aaa, aa, aa. | O o oo\n R\' M D PM | D P M G\nbhor ki bela suhani nadiya ke teerey.\n bhar ke ghagar jis ghadi main \n chalun dheere dheere.\ntujhpe | nazar | tab | jaaye | hai re hai.\n r\' r\' r\' | r\'r\'R\' | G\'R\'~S\' | R\'ÔÇª~D | P P D\njaane | kyun | baj | uthe re | kangana, \n r\' r\' | r\' | r\'r\' | r\' R\' r\' | R\' r\' R\'\nkhanak | khan | khan | khanak | khan | khan\n DND | RS | ND | PDP | MG | RG\npiya to seÔÇª.\n','Notes---Sargam-Piya-to-se-naina-lage-re');
INSERT INTO `music_sargams` (`id`,`song_names`,`sargam`,`url`) VALUES (454,'Piya Re Piya Re - Notes & Sargam','Sargam for song: Piya Re Piya Re\n Musician and Singer : Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan\n Album : Non-filmi Music Video (1997)\nA beautiful composition by Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan and equally beautiful picturisation with Sharbani Mukherjee and Pravin Dabas on screen.┬á One of the most favourite romantic songs of people who were in their teens and youth during 1990ÔÇÖs.\nEnjoy!\nIn the process of producing Sargam notations of a song, this song I quote as an example of how you can begin playing a song from an Interlude and then come back to the beginning with correct note.\nSargam for this song could be produced in any scale of flute because it contains a clue.The clue is the Interlude Sargam that goes like MPN DPN DP Mg Rg Rg R S.┬á So even if you do not get to find the first note of the song, you can start with this Interlude and then automatically, you end up playing the correct notes for the Antara which will eventually take you to play the correct first note for the word ÔÇ£PiyaÔÇØ that is ÔÇ£MaÔÇØ.\n┬á\n','Notes---Sargam-Piya-Re-Piya-Re');
INSERT INTO `music_sargams` (`id`,`song_names`,`sargam`,`url`) VALUES (455,'Phoolon Ka Taron Ka - Notes & Sargam','Sargam notations for\n Song : Phoolon Ka Taron Ka\n Movie : Hare Rama Hare Krishna (1971)\n Singer : Lata Mangeshkar / Kishore Kumar\n Musician : R. D. Burman\n Lyricist : Anand Bakshi\n(Sargam produced on C# Flute)\nSimplicity of this evergreen composition is its highlight.┬á And perhaps that has what made this song immortal.┬á Written by Anand Bakshi and composed by RD Burman, this song has two versions, one is sung by Lata Mangeshkar and the other is sung by Kishore Kumar.┬á Both versions are as popular as they were at the time of release nearly 5 decades ago.┬á The song depicts bonding between a brother and a sister, and is a must to hum, especially, on Rakhi / Rakshabandhan festival in India.\nPlaying this song on flute or any other instrument is very easy as it contains no flat notes.┬á If you play it on C# scale, then only Dha and Ni are played at Lower Octave (Mandr Saptak).\nHowever, one should not hurry to play the notes at one go.┬á It is advised that you should take the above notations as guideline and gradually build up speed that is required to play the song.┬á ┬áEven at a very slow yet steady pace, these notations will sound magical and touch the hearts of the listeners.\n','Notes---Sargam-Phoolon-Ka-Taron-Ka');
